Description. 13 ovigerous and 7 preparatory females, 8.6 –13.0 mm (
Fig. 18
). Carapace length 0.18–0.20 times total body length, 1.1–1.2 times greatest width, latter being 1.1–1.2 times depth; frontal margin not serrated, except for a few specimens having very weakly serrated frontal margin; antennal notch and lower region forming large, somewhat triangular sinus; anterolateral angle with prominent tooth directed forward, succeeded by a series of teeth on inferior margin; pereon 1.2–1.5 times carapace. Pleon 0.53–0.60 times total animal length. Dorso-posterior end of pleonite 5 with 0 or 2 thin long setae.
